	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Does the PowerPak and/or the Everdrive N8 support 4-screen?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />My consoles are all packed away and I can't test this myself right now, so I figured I'd ask you guys. With so few 4-screen games in existence, did the creators of the 2 most famous NES flash carts bother implementing this into their designs? Has anyone tested it?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Great Hierophant</b> [ Sat Jan 03, 2015 10:49 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Does the PowerPak and/or the Everdrive N8 support 4-scre</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />They do, but thefox's save state PowerPak mappers do not, so use loopy's or the official Mapper 4.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Sat Jan 03, 2015 11:01 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Does the PowerPak and/or the Everdrive N8 support 4-scre</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Good to know, thanks!<br /><br />I wonder if it's possible to use different configurations from the commercial 4-screen games that were released, such as mappers other than the MMC3, CHR-RAM instead of ROM or 8Kb of WRAM along with the 4-screen. From your response it looks like the support for 4-screen is hardwired to the MMC3, which would be a bit of a let down considering that this is a feature that could technically be implemented in any cartridge.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
